2.2. Term. This Agreement shall commence on the Effective Date and shall continue for a period of _____ years (the "Initial Term"), unless earlier terminated in accordance with Section 8. Upon expiration of the Initial Term, this Agreement shall automatically renew for successive one-year periods (each, a "Renewal Term") unless either Party provides written notice of non-renewal at least sixty (60) days prior to the end of the then-current term.

2.3. Authority. The Owner hereby grants the Broker the authority to:
(a) Market and advertise the Vessel for charter
(b) Negotiate charter terms with potential charterers
(c) Execute charter agreements on behalf of the Owner
(d) Collect charter fees and APA
(e) Coordinate charter arrangements
(f) Engage in all reasonable activities necessary to fulfill its obligations under this Agreement

3. BROKER'S COMMISSION

3.1. Commission Structure:
(a) Standard Charter Commission: The Broker shall earn a commission equal to fifteen percent (15%) of the gross Charter Fee for each Charter booked during the Term.
(b) Special Marketing Campaign Commission: For Charters booked through special marketing campaigns or promotions, the Broker may earn up to twenty percent (20%) of the gross Charter Fee, subject to prior written agreement between the Parties.
(c) Additional Services Commission: The Broker shall earn a commission of ten percent (10%) on all ancillary services arranged by the Broker and accepted by the charterer.

3.2. Commission Payment Terms:
(a) Earning of Commission: Commission is earned when the Charter Fee is collected from the charterer.
(b) Payment Timing: The Owner shall pay the Commission within seven (7) business days of the Broker's receipt of the Charter Fee.
(c) Payment Method: All Commission payments shall be made by wire transfer to the Broker's designated account:
Bank: _____________________________________
Account Name: _____________________________
Account Number: ___________________________
Routing/Swift: ____________________________

3.3. Commission Protection:
(a) Repeat Bookings: The Owner shall pay the Commission on all repeat bookings from clients introduced by the Broker for a period of twenty-four (24) months following the initial introduction or the termination of this Agreement, whichever is later.
(b) Direct Bookings: If a client introduced by the Broker contacts the Owner directly, the Owner shall:
    (i) Immediately notify the Broker
    (ii) Refer the client back to the Broker
    (iii) Pay the full Commission if a Charter is booked

4. BROKER'S RESPONSIBILITIES

4.1. Marketing Services. The Broker shall:
(a) Develop and implement a comprehensive marketing strategy for the Vessel
(b) Create and maintain professional marketing materials
(c) List the Vessel on the Broker's websites and marketing platforms
(d) Represent the Vessel at yacht shows and industry events
(e) Maintain a network of industry contacts to promote the Vessel
(f) Provide regular marketing activity reports to the Owner

4.2. Charter Management. The Broker shall:
(a) Handle all charter inquiries professionally and promptly
(b) Negotiate charter terms in the Owner's best interest
(c) Prepare and execute charter documentation
(d) Conduct appropriate client screening and verification
(e) Process all charter payments through secure channels
(f) Coordinate charter logistics and planning
(g) Maintain accurate records of all charter activities

4.3. Professional Standards. The Broker shall:
(a) Maintain active IYBA membership
(b) Adhere to the IYBA Code of Ethics
(c) Maintain all required licenses and permits
(d) Carry appropriate insurance coverage
(e) Comply with all applicable laws and regulations
(f) Protect the Owner's interests and reputation
(g) Maintain confidentiality of sensitive information

5. OWNER'S RESPONSIBILITIES

5.1. Vessel Information. The Owner shall:
(a) Provide accurate and complete vessel specifications
(b) Supply high-quality photographs and videos
(c) Update the availability calendar promptly
(d) Disclose any material changes to vessel condition
(e) Provide copies of all required certificates and documentation
(f) Maintain accurate crew information and qualifications

5.2. Vessel Maintenance. The Owner shall:
(a) Maintain the Vessel in charter-ready condition
(b) Keep all certificates and licenses current
(c) Maintain comprehensive insurance coverage
(d) Ensure crew meets all required standards
(e) Conduct regular maintenance and updates
(f) Address any deficiencies promptly

5.3. Charter Operations. The Owner shall:
(a) Honor all confirmed charter bookings
(b) Maintain consistent pricing structure
(c) Provide standard charter inventory
(d) Ensure proper crew service standards
(e) Comply with all charter agreement terms
(f) Address charter-related issues promptly

