8. TERMINATION

8.1. Termination Rights:
(a) Either Party may terminate this Agreement:
    (i) Upon sixty (60) days written notice
    (ii) Immediately for material breach
    (iii) Upon bankruptcy or insolvency of the other Party
(b) The Owner may terminate immediately if:
    (i) Broker loses IYBA membership
    (ii) Broker loses required licenses
    (iii) Broker fails to maintain insurance
(c) The Broker may terminate immediately if:
    (i) Vessel becomes unseaworthy
    (ii) Owner fails to maintain insurance
    (iii) Owner breaches charter agreements

8.2. Post-Termination:
(a) Complete existing charter commitments
(b) Settle outstanding commissions
(c) Return marketing materials
(d) Remove Vessel from marketing channels
(e) Maintain commission protection period
(f) Preserve confidentiality obligations

9. DISPUTE RESOLUTION

9.1. Resolution Process:
(a) Direct Negotiation:
    - Parties shall negotiate in good faith
    - Minimum 30-day negotiation period
(b) Mediation:
    - Through IYBA mediation services
    - Costs shared equally
(c) Binding Arbitration:
    - In Miami, Florida
    - Under IYBA arbitration rules
    - Single arbitrator
    - Costs borne by losing party

9.2. Governing Law and Jurisdiction:
(a) This Agreement shall be governed by the laws of the State of Florida
(b) Exclusive jurisdiction in the courts of Miami-Dade County, Florida
(c) Each Party submits to such jurisdiction

10. FORCE MAJEURE

10.1. Neither Party shall be liable for any failure or delay in performance due to Force Majeure Events, including but not limited to:
(a) Natural disasters
(b) War or terrorism
(c) Government actions
(d) Pandemics or epidemics
(e) Labor disputes
(f) Other events beyond reasonable control

10.2. The affected Party shall:
(a) Notify the other Party promptly
(b) Use reasonable efforts to mitigate
(c) Resume performance when possible

11. CONFIDENTIALITY

11.1. Each Party agrees to maintain the confidentiality of:
(a) Charter client details
(b) Financial terms and rates
(c) Vessel information
(d) Operational details
(e) Business strategies
(f) Proprietary information

11.2. Exceptions:
(a) Information in public domain
(b) Required by law or regulation
(c) Necessary for charter operations

12. MISCELLANEOUS

12.1. Entire Agreement:
This Agreement constitutes the entire agreement between the Parties and supersedes all prior agreements.

12.2. Amendments:
Any amendments must be in writing and signed by both Parties.

12.3. Assignment:
Neither Party may assign this Agreement without written consent.

12.4. Notices:
All notices shall be in writing and delivered to the addresses stated above.

12.5. Severability:
If any provision is invalid, the remainder shall remain in effect.

12.6. Counterparts:
This Agreement may be executed in counterparts.

